    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2192003,
      "reputation" : 51,
      "user_id" : 1938760,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/07eefb1d5d35199dc5223aa353333fce?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Lou Prado",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1938760/lou-prado"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 5,
    "last_activity_date" : 1425874050,
    "creation_date" : 1425874050,
    "answer_id" : 28935103,
    "question_id" : 20537845,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>After 8 hours on this problem I feel obliged to share the cause. My /etc/hosts was bad. </p>\n\n<p>Make sure you can ping localhost and that it is defined to 127.0.0.1. AS expects to connect to localhost:8600.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1260243,
      "reputation" : 1130,
      "user_id" : 1796769,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/bdfa04b7d924bc53f42aff946074acb8?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Jalkin",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1796769/jalkin"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1426360296,
    "creation_date" : 1426360296,
    "answer_id" : 29053069,
    "question_id" : 20537845,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I had this problem; In Android Studio I accidentally hit <strong>Run > 'Debug App'</strong> instead of <strong>Run> Run 'App'</strong> . I solved the problem. In my case I had to get the application to launch successfully in DEBUG mode. Here were my steps-</p>\n\n<p>1) The android device needs to be able to connect to the development PC on port 8600. This connection was being disallowed by my firewall configuration. I turned off the firewall. Once confirmed <strong><em>I created a firewall rule to allow connectivity between the devices on port 8600</em></strong>. </p>\n\n<p>2) To validate that the port is available, you can go into Android Studio, \n<strong>Run > Attach debugger to Android Process</strong>. This will cause the android device application launched in DEBUG mode to connect to your Android Studio development PC. </p>\n\n<p>3) Once the app has launched once, you can go back and <strong>Run > Run 'App'</strong> and you will no longer get the annoying screen 'WAITING for DEBUGGER'.</p>\n\n<p>4) And you can also <strong>Run> Debug 'App'</strong>. The device will say \"Waiting for Debugger\" for a moment and then Android Studio will start up a Debugger Console and help you debug your android device app remotely!</p>\n\n<p>Good luck</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 5899071,
      "reputation" : 311,
      "user_id" : 4643247,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-ssEXYzz7Pfo/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAKc/ULZq2b4YTPw/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "Raghav Thakkar",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4643247/raghav-thakkar"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1433529168,
    "creation_date" : 1433529168,
    "answer_id" : 30673478,
    "question_id" : 20537845,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>1) Clear android studio cache memory from file->Invalid cache/restart.</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>2) After restarting the android studio please restart android emulator.</p>\n"
